<h2>Ski holiday - Snow Guarantee</h2>
<p>Our expert-selected ski resorts across Europe and Canada are renowned for incredible snow records and are often selected for their high-altitude, enhancing the chances of good quality snow. We offer our skiing holidays during the months that reflect these snowy conditions and have tailored our holidays to reflect our 90 years of travel knowledge to ensure you have the best experience. </p>
<p>But if there's no Snow? S’no problem! If you’ve booked a package holiday with us – including travel from the UK, accommodation and transport (flights, trains or self-drive) and the resort you're staying in has less than 25% of their ski runs open due to lack of snow, we’ll organise transport to get you to and from a resort that has better skiing conditions for any affected days covered by your lift pass. Worried about losing out on unused lift passes or ski lessons that can’t go ahead? If you’ve booked these through us, we’ll refund you.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span><a data-udi="umb://document/1e6f5e817a4f4af3b851984b9c3fa71c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1e6f5e817a4f4af3b851984b9c3fa71c}" class="c-btn">Ski deals</a> <a data-udi="umb://document/6a8b15733cdd470bb0d866187156d07d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6a8b15733cdd470bb0d866187156d07d}" class="c-btn">Ski holidays</a></span></p>
<h3><span>Terms &amp; Conditions: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The Inghams Snow Guarantee covers all of our ski holidays between December 2024 and April 2025, and between December 2025 and April 2026, with the exception of bookings made within 14 days of travel. </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Our Snow Guarantee is applicable from the arrival day, but we won’t organise transport until your first full ski day.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Snow conditions and piste/run availability will be determined using the data published from: <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.skiresort.info/snow-reports/" target="_blank" title="Snow Report">Snow report</a> - <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.skiresort.info/snow-reports/" target="_blank" title="Snow reports">current snow reports</a>, or if data cannot be obtained from this source, we will use the official resort data. No other sources will be used or considered, and we'll use the live conditions on the day of your arrival.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>If fewer than 25% of runs are open in the resort you are staying in due to lack of snow, we will organise transport to and from a nearby resort that is open, free of charge, for any affected days covered by your lift pass (where local transport is not available and covered by your lift pass). If there isn't an accessible resort that is open to non-resident guests within two hours of your location, we won't be able to run a transport service.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you’ve booked your ski lessons through Inghams, we’ll organise a refund for any ski lessons that can’t go ahead due to the resort being closed once you’ve arrived back in the UK.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you’ve booked your lift passes through Inghams, we’ll do our best to organise replacement passes for the new resort if it isn’t covered by your existing pass. If we’re unable to do so, we’ll organise a refund once you've arrived back in the UK.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you haven’t booked your ski lessons or lift passes through Inghams, we won’t be able to give you a refund, but we’ll do our best to help make alternative arrangements for your new resort and you’ll be able to use our transport services.</p>
</li>
<li>Where snow conditions and piste/run availability using the above sources are such that less than 25% of runs in your booked resort are available in the 5 days prior to your departure, and there is no accessible resort that is open to non-resident guests within two hours of your location that we can transport you to, we will contact you to discuss alternative options. This may include a change of resort or departure date to one within the same ski season.</li>
</ul>
<p>This snow guarantee applies to ski holidays only and not Inghams Lapland activity holidays. Please be reassured that in Lapland if snow is too poor to allow for your booked activities to take place, we will contact you about your options, including refunds where applicable.</p>
